## Culture

The [Edmonton City Centre](/Edmonton_City_Centre) complex houses not only a retail mall but also the English and French language studios for [CBC/Radio-Canada](/Ici_Radio-Canada_T%C3%A9l%C3%A9), Canada's national public broadcaster. This dual-language presence underscores the multicultural fabric of the city.

Alberta is home to an extensive network of over 100 francophone non-profit organizations, each contributing to the vitality and diversity of the province's cultural landscape. These organizations operate across a wide spectrum of fields, from arts and education to community development and social services. La Cité Francophone, situated in the [Bonnie Doon](/Bonnie_Doon,_Edmonton) neighborhood of Edmonton, adjacent to the Campus Saint-Jean, serves as a pivotal provincial hub for Franco-Albertan organizations. It is also the venue for the annual Flying Canoë Volant festival, a vibrant celebration of winter culture and storytelling.

In the realm of performing arts, L'Unithéâtre in Edmonton and the Société de Théâtre present a repertoire of French-language theatrical works, enriching the province's cultural offerings. The [Chorale Saint-Jean](/Chorale_Saint-Jean) contributes to the musical landscape with its performances of French choral music. Additionally, numerous French Canadian folk dancing troupes embark on tours throughout the province, sharing traditional and contemporary dance forms. The Centre d’arts visuels de l’Alberta provides a dedicated space for francophone artists and artisans to showcase their work, fostering artistic expression and exchange. The annual Franco-Alberta Festival serves as a major platform for celebrating French language and culture, bringing together communities from across the province. The [Regroupement artistique francophone de l'Alberta](/Regroupement_artistique_francophone_de_l%27Alberta) plays a crucial role in organizing events and providing professional development opportunities for francophone artists, ensuring the continued growth and vibrancy of the arts sector.

