## Media

Francophones residing in Alberta have access to broadcast media primarily through the television and radio services provided by the [Société Radio-Canada](/Soci%C3%A9t%C3%A9_Radio-Canada), the French-language division of the [Canadian Broadcasting Corporation](/Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation). This includes programming from [Ici Radio-Canada Télé](/Ici_Radio-Canada_T%C3%A9l%C3%A9)'s station [CBXFT-DT](/CBXFT-DT), the radio service [Ici Radio-Canada Première](/Ici_Radio-Canada_Premi%C3%A8re) via its station [CHFA-FM](/CHFA-FM), and the music service [Ici Musique](/Ici_Musique) broadcast on [CBCX-FM](/CBCX-FM). Complementing these national services, francophone community radio stations operate in Edmonton ([CFED-FM](/CFED-FM)) and [Plamondon, Alberta](/Plamondon,_Alberta) ([CHPL-FM](/CHPL-FM)). A third community radio station, [CKRP-FM](/CKRP-FM) located in [Falher, Alberta](/Falher,_Alberta), ceased operations in 2017.

In terms of print media, the weekly French-language newspaper *Le Franco* serves the province, providing news, commentary, and cultural content tailored to the Franco-Albertan community.

