## Notes

*   The figures cited represent Albertans who reported French as their mother tongue. The government of Alberta defines a Franco-Albertan as a francophone resident of the province [2].
*   In this context, "linguistic minority population" specifically refers to anglophones or francophones, as English and French are recognized as the [official languages of Canada](/Official_languages_of_Canada).

